        <abstract> 
<p>On Huxley’s article for <hi rend="italic">Contemporary Review</hi> [see <hi rend="doubleUnderline">7977</hi>] confuting Mivart. It has cheered him,</p> 
            <p>for he is very low about his mother’s state.</p>
            <p>Is also in detestable position with "my lord and master", A. S. Ayrton. JDH has denounced him to the [First] Lord of the Treasury [W. E. Gladstone] for his conduct.</p>
        </abstract>
